metadata.name: MQ21V_ I
metadata.description:
MQ-21 was a concept for a remotely piloted aircraft system (RPAS).

It can be controllable via satellite links from anywhere on Earth to collect massive amounts of intelligence data from unreachable areas.

Also, Biomimetic technology helps this drone to have a safe and perfect landing at the target, and it will become a pod mobile mapping system to capture data from the ground.

Check out full project here:
https://www.artstation.com/artwork/9mBnby
